g.text: Using matrix linear models to study variation in triglyceride composition

Y= XBZT+ E, with V (vec(E)) = Σ ⊗Iwhere• Yn×mis the matrix of the output data arranged in n samples and m typesof measurements (i.e., triglyceride levels)• Xn×pis the matrix of covariates composed of n samples and p independentvariables (e.g.,phenotypestatus, whether they were taking fish oil)• Zm×qis the matrix of measurement attributes composed of m measurementsand q attribute variables (e.g., information about triglycerides)• Bp×qis the matrix of coefficients (i.e., can be interpreted as interactionsbetweenZandXcovariates)• Eis random error assumed to have mean zero, independent across individuals,but possibly correlated across outcomes
